---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Documentation - Backlog Chef" description="Complete documentation for Backlog Chef - Transform meetings into high-quality Product Backlogs">
  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-slate-900">Documentation</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-12">
        Everything you need to know about Backlog Chef - from CLI commands to the web interface, from the 8-step pipeline to RAG-powered semantic search.
      </p>

      <!-- Quick Navigation -->
      <nav class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Quick Navigation</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-sm">
          <a href="#vision" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Vision</a>
          <a href="#pipeline" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">8-Step Pipeline</a>
          <a href="#cli" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">CLI Commands</a>
          <a href="#web" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Web Interface</a>
          <a href="#rag" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">RAG System</a>
          <a href="#config" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Configuration</a>
          <a href="#tech" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Tech Stack</a>
          <a href="#roadmap" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Roadmap</a>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Vision -->
      <section id="vision" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">Vision</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Backlog Chef is an <strong>AI-powered system that transforms Scrum refinement meetings into structured, high-quality Product Backlog Items</strong> with built-in quality assurance, context enrichment, and stakeholder intelligence.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">Key Differentiators</h3>
          <ul class="text-slate-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Domain-Specific:</strong> Built for Agile/Scrum, not generic transcription</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Quality Built-In:</strong> Confidence scoring prevents incomplete requirements</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Actionable:</strong> Generates questions, proposals, and finds similar work</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Integrated:</strong> Works with Fireflies, Jira, Azure DevOps, Confluence via MCP</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Learning System:</strong> Improves with your team's history and patterns</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 8-Step Pipeline -->
      <section id="pipeline" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">8-Step Intelligence Pipeline</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6">
          Every transcript goes through our sophisticated processing pipeline. Each step builds on the previous one to ensure maximum quality and completeness.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 1</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Event Detection</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Identifies meeting type (refinement, planning, retrospective) using CLI flags, title parsing, or LLM inference. Provides confidence scoring for detection method.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 2</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Extract Candidate PBIs</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Parses transcript for potential backlog items. Identifies business value, scope, actors, and preliminary structure extraction.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-green-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-green-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 3</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Score Confidence</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Evaluates completeness against quality checklist. Scores completeness, clarity, actionability, and testability. Identifies missing elements.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-green-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-green-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 4</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Enrich with Context</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Searches similar work, past decisions, and technical documentation using RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation). Uses frontmatter-based document filtering to prevent duplicate work and identify related constraints.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-yellow-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 5</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Check Risks & Conflicts</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Detects dependencies, scope creep, blockers, and integration risks. Flags complexity markers and affected systems automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-yellow-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 6</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Generate Questions + Proposals</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Creates actionable questions with suggested answers. Routes to appropriate stakeholders, proposes clarifications, and suggests risk mitigation strategies.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-purple-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-purple-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 7</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Run Readiness Checker</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Validates against your team's custom Definition of Ready criteria. Supports custom DoR configuration per team, quality gate enforcement, and gap identification.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-purple-500">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
              <span class="bg-purple-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3">Step 8</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Final Output</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Formats PBIs for multiple destinations: Markdown (primary), DevOps (Azure DevOps format), Obsidian (note-taking with wiki links), Confluence (wiki), and JSON (raw data).
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CLI Commands -->
      <section id="cli" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">CLI Commands</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6">
          Backlog Chef provides 10 powerful CLI commands for complete control over your backlog processing workflow.
        </p>

        <!-- Processing Commands -->
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-slate-900">Processing Commands</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef process &lt;source&gt;</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Main command for processing meeting transcripts through the 8-step pipeline. Accepts file paths, Fireflies meeting IDs, or Fireflies URLs.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --hitl (Human-in-the-loop mode), --workflow &lt;profile&gt;, --output &lt;format&gt;
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef resume [pipeline-id]</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Resume paused pipelines from where they left off. Interactive selection if no ID provided.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --hitl, --output &lt;format&gt;
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef status</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Display pipeline status for all tracked sources. Shows running, paused, completed, and error states.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --verbose, --json
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Configuration Commands -->
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-slate-900">Configuration Commands</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef init</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Initialize Backlog Chef in a project. Creates documentation folder structure, copies templates, generates configuration files.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --minimal, --with-rag, --silent
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef setup</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Interactive setup wizard for first-time configuration. Configures API keys, tests connections, sets up environment.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --global, --local, --force, --silent
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Output Commands -->
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-slate-900">Output Commands</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef export [options]</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Export PBIs from pipeline output to markdown files. Export by ID, by source, or all pending.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --id &lt;pbi-id&gt;, --source &lt;source&gt;, --all, --dry-run, --force, --dest &lt;path&gt;
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef format &lt;source&gt; --target &lt;format&gt;</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Regenerate PBI output in different formats without re-running the pipeline. Preserves original data.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Formats:</strong> devops, obsidian, confluence, json, markdown
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RAG Commands -->
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-slate-900">RAG Commands</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef rag index [path]</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Index documentation for semantic search. Uses ChromaDB vector store with configurable chunking strategy.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --watch, --strategy &lt;semantic|fixed|recursive&gt;, --include-pbis
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef rag query "&lt;query&gt;"</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Search indexed documents semantically using natural language queries.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --top-k &lt;n&gt;, --min-score &lt;0-1&gt;, --json
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Validation Commands -->
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-slate-900">Validation Commands</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <code class="text-green-400 font-mono text-lg">chef validate docs [path]</code>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-2 text-sm">
              Validate documentation against frontmatter schema. Checks for required fields, valid types, and proper structure.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-slate-400 text-xs">
              <strong>Options:</strong> --strict, --include-warnings, --report &lt;path&gt;, --json
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Web Interface -->
      <section id="web" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">Web Interface</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6">
          A modern Astro-powered web interface for visual PBI management, semantic search, and meeting browsing.
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">PBI Browser</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Multi-view support with Table, Card Grid, and Kanban views. Filter tabs for All, Active, Planned, Completed. Priority-based sorting and domain tag filtering.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/app/pbis</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">Semantic Search</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Search across all documentation with specialized tabs: Constraints, Patterns, Similar Work, Tech Docs, Business Docs, Examples, Deprecated.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/app/search</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">Meetings Browser</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Browse all processed meetings with metadata display and links to transcripts and summaries.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/app/meetings</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">Transcript Viewer</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Full meeting transcripts with speaker identification and timestamp navigation.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/app/transcripts</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">Export Mapping</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Configure PBI field mappings for different output formats with a property mapping table editor.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/app/export-mapping</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white p-5 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">RAG API</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">REST API for context retrieval with specialized endpoints for constraints, patterns, similar work, and more.</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2 block">/api/rag/*</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- RAG System -->
      <section id="rag" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">RAG System</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6">
          Retrieval-Augmented Generation powers Step 4 (Context Enrichment) and the Semantic Search feature.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Vector Store Configuration</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700">
            <li><strong>Provider:</strong> ChromaDB (local) with Pinecone support planned</li>
            <li><strong>Embedding Model:</strong> Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dimensions, 80MB, fast)</li>
            <li><strong>Chunking Strategy:</strong> Semantic (configurable: fixed, recursive)</li>
            <li><strong>Chunk Settings:</strong> Min 100 chars, Max 500 chars, 50 char overlap</li>
            <li><strong>Retrieval:</strong> Top-K (default 5), min similarity 0.3</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Specialized Search Endpoints</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/constraints</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">ADRs, policies, binding decisions</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/patterns</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Architectural and design patterns</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/similar-work</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Completed PBIs and related items</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/tech-docs</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Technical documentation</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/business</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Business documentation</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/examples</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Code and implementation examples</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/deprecated</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Deprecated patterns to avoid</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded">
              <code class="text-blue-600">/api/rag/by-domain</code>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1">Domain-organized search</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Frontmatter Schema</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">All documents use YAML frontmatter for intelligent filtering in Step 4:</p>
          <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>---
type: adr | policy | architecture | specification | reference | business | pbi | pact | guide
id: XXX-NNN
title: "Document Title"
status: active | draft | deprecated
domain: [authentication, pipeline, integration]
decision_type: constraint | recommendation | pattern | example
keywords: [explicit, search, terms]
---</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Configuration -->
      <section id="config" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">Configuration</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6">
          Backlog Chef is fully configuration-driven with multiple workflow profiles and team-specific settings.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Workflow Profiles</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement.yaml</code> - Standard refinement workflow</li>
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement-minimal.yaml</code> - Lightweight version</li>
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement-full.yaml</code> - All features enabled</li>
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement-questions-only.yaml</code> - Questions focus</li>
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement-risk-focused.yaml</code> - Risk emphasis</li>
              <li><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">refinement-binary-readiness.yaml</code> - Simple ready/not-ready</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Definition of Ready</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Team-specific DoR configuration files</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Multi-role workflows</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Customizable criteria per team</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Enforcement levels: critical, high, medium</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Localization support (e.g., Dutch)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Output Formats</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
              <li><strong>DevOps:</strong> Azure DevOps work item format</li>
              <li><strong>Obsidian:</strong> Markdown with wiki links</li>
              <li><strong>Confluence:</strong> Wiki-ready format</li>
              <li><strong>JSON:</strong> Raw structured data</li>
              <li><strong>Markdown:</strong> Standard documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Main Config File</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm mb-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">backlog-chef.config.yaml</code></p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-slate-600 text-sm">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Project metadata</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Server settings (web: 4321, chroma: 8000)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Path configuration</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ RAG settings</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Fireflies integration</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Tech Stack -->
      <section id="tech" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900 border-b-2 border-blue-600 pb-2">Technology Stack</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">CLI (MVP)</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700">
              <li><strong>Language:</strong> TypeScript/Node.js</li>
              <li><strong>AI Engine:</strong> Anthropic Claude API</li>
              <li><strong>Integration:</strong> Model Context Protocol (MCP)</li>
              <li><strong>Vector Store:</strong> ChromaDB</li>
              <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Local JSON + .chef/ state folder</li>
              <li><strong>Templating:</strong> Handlebars</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
